This gem of a restaurant is just around the block from my apartment, and despite passing by its unassuming exterior dozens of time since moving to Brooklyn, I never walked in to give it a try.  I am kicking myself now, because I have been missing out on some of the most authentic and delicious Indian food that I've ever eaten.  It was a good sign from the very beginning when everything on the menu looked like something I wanted to try.  My friend and I decided on the poori with chickpeas bengali style for appetizer and the classic chicken tikka masala and the beef karahi for entrees based on the recommendation of the friendly waiter.  The food came piping hot, aesthetically great looking, and turned out to be just as tasty as they appeared.  The garlic naan that complemented the meal was also an excellent highlight;a simple dish done right.  The main takeaway was how authentic everything tasted--the chefs really know their craft here.  I saw that Bombay grill offers take-out and deliveries, and that seemed to comprise the bulk of their business during the quiet meal we had there.  I highly recommend that you give this place a visit--the atmosphere was chill, friendly, and in my opinion, the food seemed to be best enjoyed straight out of the kitchen.  I definitely look forward to future visits to try out the rest of their menu.
